ll be replaced by the\r\u001b[4d; pool name ('www' here)\r\u001b[5d[www]\r\u001b[7d; Per pool prefix\r\u001b[8d; It only applies on the following directives:\r\u001b[9d; - 'access.log'\r\u001b[10d; - 'slowlog'\r\u001b[11d; - 'listen' (unixsocket)\r\u001b[12d; - 'chroot'\r\u001b[13d; - 'chdir'\r\u001b[14d; - 'php_values'\r\u001b[15d; - 'php_admin_values'\r\u001b[16d; When not set, the global prefix (or /usr) applies instead.\r\u001b[17d; Note: This directive can also be relative to the global prefix.\r\u001b[18d; Default Value: none\r\u001b[19d;prefix = /path/to/pools/$pool\r\u001b[21d; Unix user/group of the child processes. This can be used only if the master\r\u001b[22d; process running user is root. It is set after the child process is created.\r\u001b[23d; The user and group can be specified either by their name or by their numeric\r\u001b[24d; IDs.\r\u001b[25d; Note: If the user is root, the executable needs to be started with\r\u001b[26d;\u001b[9G--allow-to-run-as-root option to work.\r\u001b[27d; Default Values: The user is set to master process running user by default.\r\u001b[28d;\u001b[28;19HIf the group is not set, the user's group is used.\r\u001b[29duser = http\r\u001b[30dgroup = http\r\u001b[32d; The address on which to accept FastCGI requests.\r\u001b[33d; Valid syntaxes are:\r\u001b[34d;   'ip.add.re.ss:port'    - to listen on a TCP socket to a specific IPv4 address on\r\u001b[35d;\u001b[35;30Ha specific port;\r\u001b[36d;   '[ip:6:addr:ess]:port' - to listen on a TCP socket to a specific IPv6 address on\r\u001b[37d;\u001b[37;30Ha specific port;\r\u001b[38d;   'port'\u001b[38;28H- to listen on a TCP socket to all addresses\r\u001b[39d;\u001b[39;30H(IPv6 and IPv4-mapped) on a specific port;\r\u001b[40d;   '/path/to/unix/socket' - to listen on a unix socket.\r\u001b[41d; Note: This value is mandatory.\r\u001b[42dlisten = /run/php-fpm/php-fpm.sock\r\u001b[44d; Set listen(2) backlog.\r\u001b[45d; Default Value: 511 (-1 on Linux, FreeBSD and OpenBSD)\r\u0